00:45:17.000 --> 00:45:20.000
You sell the same amount of goods as before,

00:45:20.000 --> 00:45:23.000
but at a higher price.

00:45:23.000 --> 00:45:26.000
And the standard of the added value increases

00:45:26.000 --> 00:45:29.000
and the enterprise feels euphoria

00:45:29.000 --> 00:45:32.000
from getting additional profit.

00:45:32.000 --> 00:45:35.000
But if your goods are elastic

00:45:35.000 --> 00:45:38.000
and more and more high-elastic,

00:45:38.000 --> 00:45:41.000
then the price increase is not a good condition.

00:45:41.000 --> 00:45:44.000
The thing is that if you are not a monopolist

00:45:44.000 --> 00:45:47.000
and you are in a state of conspiracy,

00:45:47.000 --> 00:45:50.000
then the price increase leads to the fact

00:45:50.000 --> 00:45:53.000
that the consumers stop buying the goods

00:45:53.000 --> 00:45:56.000
and start buying the goods from your competitors

00:45:56.000 --> 00:45:59.000
who did not raise the price.

00:45:59.000 --> 00:46:02.000
The sale of elastic goods

00:46:02.000 --> 00:46:05.000
in order to get more profit,

00:46:05.000 --> 00:46:08.000
as you remember,

00:46:08.000 --> 00:46:11.000
should not increase the price,

00:46:11.000 --> 00:46:14.000
but should decrease the price.

00:46:14.000 --> 00:46:17.000
When we talk about the standard of the added value,

00:46:17.000 --> 00:46:20.000
we are talking about the price increase.

00:46:20.000 --> 00:46:23.000
The price increase is good for non-elastic goods

00:46:23.000 --> 00:46:26.000
or for elastic goods

00:46:26.000 --> 00:46:29.000
that are still produced by monopolists

00:46:29.000 --> 00:46:32.000
or monopolists.

00:46:32.000 --> 00:46:35.000
Then, due to these economic forms,

00:46:35.000 --> 00:46:38.000
the goods become non-elastic

00:46:38.000 --> 00:46:41.000
and the price increases.

00:46:41.000 --> 00:46:44.000
And if you are not a very large enterprise

00:46:44.000 --> 00:46:47.000
and you cannot be a monopolist or a monopolist,

00:46:47.000 --> 00:46:50.000
but you are in a competitive environment,

00:46:50.000 --> 00:46:53.000
you need to remember

00:46:53.000 --> 00:46:56.000
that the price increase

00:46:56.000 --> 00:46:59.000
is not the only way

00:46:59.000 --> 00:47:02.000
to get profit from the business.

00:47:02.000 --> 00:47:05.000
You can get profit from the business

00:47:05.000 --> 00:47:08.000
by reducing the price,

00:47:08.000 --> 00:47:11.000
reducing the standard of the added value,

00:47:11.000 --> 00:47:14.000
but increasing the volume of the produced goods.

00:47:14.000 --> 00:47:17.000
And the total profit you get

00:47:17.000 --> 00:47:20.000
from the production of the standard of the added value

00:47:20.000 --> 00:47:23.000
for the number of produced goods will increase.

00:47:23.000 --> 00:47:26.000
So, if you are not an oligopolist

00:47:26.000 --> 00:47:29.000
and not a monopolist,

00:47:29.000 --> 00:47:32.000
do not despair.

00:47:32.000 --> 00:47:35.000
You can reduce the price

00:47:35.000 --> 00:47:38.000
and then you will live perfectly

00:47:38.000 --> 00:47:41.000
without increasing the price.

00:47:41.000 --> 00:47:44.000
For the coverage of the current financial needs

00:47:44.000 --> 00:47:47.000
that we have just talked about,

00:47:47.000 --> 00:47:50.000
enterprises need financial resources.

00:47:50.000 --> 00:47:53.000
Where do enterprises get the financial resources

00:47:53.000 --> 00:47:56.000
to realize their needs?

00:47:56.000 --> 00:47:59.000
We have already said that the best is their own financial resources.

00:47:59.000 --> 00:48:02.000
But if they are not enough,

00:48:02.000 --> 00:48:05.000
and if they do not have enough credit

00:48:05.000 --> 00:48:08.000
that is generated by the business partners

00:48:08.000 --> 00:48:11.000
to provide them with the goods,

00:48:11.000 --> 00:48:14.000
then the enterprise, as we remember,

00:48:14.000 --> 00:48:17.000
turns to the financial market

00:48:17.000 --> 00:48:20.000
and gets the financial resources

00:48:20.000 --> 00:48:23.000
from the market

00:48:23.000 --> 00:48:26.000
in the form of a loan or a bank loan.

00:48:26.000 --> 00:48:29.000
I repeat,

00:48:29.000 --> 00:48:32.000
a loan is the obtaining of financial resources

00:48:32.000 --> 00:48:35.000
from the same business partners as you,

00:48:35.000 --> 00:48:38.000
and a loan is the obtaining of financial resources

00:48:38.000 --> 00:48:41.000
from the banks.

00:48:41.000 --> 00:48:44.000
We have already talked about this,

00:48:44.000 --> 00:48:47.000
but we have repeated it again.

00:48:47.000 --> 00:48:50.000
So, a loan or a bank loan

00:48:50.000 --> 00:48:53.000
is a way to cover the current financial needs.

00:48:53.000 --> 00:48:56.000
We are talking about short-term financial needs,

00:48:56.000 --> 00:48:59.000
so we are talking about short-term loans

00:48:59.000 --> 00:49:02.000
or short-term bank loans.

00:49:02.000 --> 00:49:05.000
In addition to these,

00:49:05.000 --> 00:49:08.000
there is an opportunity to issue a VEXEL.

00:49:08.000 --> 00:49:11.000
And these enterprises often use it.

00:49:11.000 --> 00:49:14.000
VEXEL is a very convenient form of short-term financing.

00:49:14.000 --> 00:49:17.000
The thing is that you issue VEXEL yourself.

00:49:17.000 --> 00:49:20.000
You do not have to go to any financial institution

00:49:20.000 --> 00:49:23.000
to issue a VEXEL.

00:49:23.000 --> 00:49:26.000
There is a law that regulates the content of VEXEL,

00:49:26.000 --> 00:49:29.000
which should be indicated in VEXEL.

00:49:29.000 --> 00:49:32.000
The form of VEXEL is determined by you,

00:49:32.000 --> 00:49:35.000
so that you can write VEXEL

00:49:35.000 --> 00:49:38.000
on a clean piece of paper.

00:49:38.000 --> 00:49:41.000
Only if everything that is written in VEXEL

00:49:41.000 --> 00:49:44.000
meets the requirements of the law.

00:49:44.000 --> 00:49:47.000
It is easy to issue a VEXEL,

00:49:47.000 --> 00:49:50.000
but the most important thing in VEXEL is that it is accepted.

00:49:50.000 --> 00:49:53.000
When instead of money you are allowed to take VEXEL,

00:49:53.000 --> 00:49:56.000
you are using the reputation of a reliable business partner.

00:49:56.000 --> 00:49:59.000
You are trusted and instead of money you are allowed to take VEXEL.

00:49:59.000 --> 00:50:02.000
VEXEL is an urgent payment

00:50:02.000 --> 00:50:05.000
that you promise to return

00:50:05.000 --> 00:50:08.000
after some time,

00:50:08.000 --> 00:50:11.000
which is described in VEXEL.

00:50:11.000 --> 00:50:14.000
You will be returned VEXEL,

00:50:14.000 --> 00:50:17.000
and you will be returned money

00:50:17.000 --> 00:50:20.000
with the interest rate that is described in VEXEL.

00:50:20.000 --> 00:50:23.000
If you are a reliable business partner,

00:50:23.000 --> 00:50:26.000
if you are trusted,

00:50:26.000 --> 00:50:29.000
then they will agree to take your VEXEL.

00:50:29.000 --> 00:50:32.000
If you are not reliable in business,

00:50:32.000 --> 00:50:35.000
then you will not be able to use

00:50:35.000 --> 00:50:38.000
such a form of attracting financial funds

00:50:38.000 --> 00:50:41.000
as issuing VEXELs.

00:50:42.000 --> 00:50:45.000
In addition to VEXELs,

00:50:45.000 --> 00:50:48.000
you can use factoring.

00:50:48.000 --> 00:50:51.000
This is a new form of financing,

00:50:51.000 --> 00:50:54.000
a new one in the Russian market.

00:50:54.000 --> 00:50:57.000
It does not mean that it is never used in the world.

00:50:57.000 --> 00:51:00.000
Factoring has been known for a long time in the world,

00:51:00.000 --> 00:51:03.000
and it is used in all countries,

00:51:03.000 --> 00:51:06.000
but in the Russian market it is a young form.

00:51:06.000 --> 00:51:09.000
And in terms of time,

00:51:09.000 --> 00:51:12.000
not all enterprises that are even

00:51:12.000 --> 00:51:15.000
worthy of using factoring, use it.

00:51:15.000 --> 00:51:18.000
Moreover, not everyone knows about factoring,

00:51:18.000 --> 00:51:21.000
so when we talk about it now,

00:51:21.000 --> 00:51:24.000
it is very important,

00:51:24.000 --> 00:51:27.000
because factoring has a serious future.

00:51:27.000 --> 00:51:30.000
What is factoring?

00:51:30.000 --> 00:51:33.000
I must say, so that you can clearly imagine

00:51:33.000 --> 00:51:36.000
when to turn to it.

00:51:36.000 --> 00:51:39.000
Factoring is used by production enterprises,

00:51:39.000 --> 00:51:42.000
which produce the product

00:51:42.000 --> 00:51:45.000
and then transfer it to the consumer

00:51:45.000 --> 00:51:48.000
in the form of a commodity loan.

00:51:48.000 --> 00:51:51.000
But the enterprise cannot expand the commodity loan

00:51:51.000 --> 00:51:54.000
to infinity,

00:51:54.000 --> 00:51:57.000
because it has a fixed limited amount of money.

00:51:57.000 --> 00:52:00.000
It can give a commodity loan

00:52:00.000 --> 00:52:03.000
no more than it can give,

00:52:03.000 --> 00:52:06.000
and then it will stop.

00:52:06.000 --> 00:52:09.000
And if it wants to expand its production,

00:52:09.000 --> 00:52:12.000
it needs to increase the quantity of the commodity

00:52:12.000 --> 00:52:15.000
that is provided in the form of a commodity loan.

00:52:15.000 --> 00:52:18.000
It needs money for that.

00:52:18.000 --> 00:52:21.000
And if all the lighter forms

00:52:21.000 --> 00:52:24.000
that we have been talking about today are already used,

00:52:24.000 --> 00:52:27.000
and they cannot be used anymore,

00:52:27.000 --> 00:52:30.000
then we should remember about factoring.

00:52:30.000 --> 00:52:33.000
Factoring is not a loan.

00:52:33.000 --> 00:52:36.000
It is not provided by banks,

00:52:36.000 --> 00:52:39.000
although banks sometimes participate in it,

00:52:39.000 --> 00:52:42.000
but by special factoring companies

00:52:42.000 --> 00:52:45.000
that are created with banks

00:52:45.000 --> 00:52:48.000
and provide factoring services.

00:52:48.000 --> 00:52:51.000
The essence of factoring services is that

00:52:51.000 --> 00:52:54.000
the production enterprise unloads the commodity,

00:52:54.000 --> 00:52:57.000
provides a commodity loan,

00:52:57.000 --> 00:53:00.000
and the factory company

00:53:00.000 --> 00:53:03.000
transfers the documents of the commodity unloading.

00:53:03.000 --> 00:53:06.000
And the factory company exchanges

00:53:06.000 --> 00:53:09.000
the debt that the enterprise has

00:53:09.000 --> 00:53:12.000
for the money

00:53:12.000 --> 00:53:15.000
that is needed to cover the debt.

00:53:15.000 --> 00:53:18.000
Thus, the enterprise,

00:53:18.000 --> 00:53:21.000
in fact,

00:53:21.000 --> 00:53:24.000
gets the money

00:53:24.000 --> 00:53:27.000
that it can use for further production.

00:53:27.000 --> 00:53:30.000
And it does not need to wait

00:53:30.000 --> 00:53:33.000
for the return of the money from the trading partners.

00:53:33.000 --> 00:53:36.000
The trading partners can get a very long term loan,

00:53:36.000 --> 00:53:39.000
and the enterprise gets the money right away

00:53:39.000 --> 00:53:42.000
on the fact of the realization of the commodity.

00:53:42.000 --> 00:53:45.000
It is very convenient.

00:53:45.000 --> 00:53:48.000
But all the convenience

00:53:48.000 --> 00:53:51.000
should be assumed,

00:53:51.000 --> 00:53:54.000
that the enterprise gets the money

00:53:54.000 --> 00:53:57.000
from the factoring company,

00:53:57.000 --> 00:54:00.000
and it should pay the factoring company

00:54:00.000 --> 00:54:03.000
the same way as you pay the bank

00:54:03.000 --> 00:54:06.000
a percentage of its use of credit funds.

00:54:06.000 --> 00:54:09.000
And the factoring company

00:54:09.000 --> 00:54:12.000
should pay a certain fee for the services it provides.

00:54:12.000 --> 00:54:15.000
So, if you get financial funds

00:54:15.000 --> 00:54:18.000
either from the bank

00:54:18.000 --> 00:54:21.000
or from the factoring company,

00:54:21.000 --> 00:54:24.000
all these funds are not free.

00:54:24.000 --> 00:54:27.000
There is a certain fee for them.

00:54:27.000 --> 00:54:30.000
And the bank percentage is even less than the factoring one.

00:54:30.000 --> 00:54:33.000
Therefore, the enterprise always takes the bank loan

00:54:33.000 --> 00:54:36.000
earlier than the factoring one.

00:54:36.000 --> 00:54:39.000
The factoring is the use of money.

00:54:39.000 --> 00:54:42.000
The bank provides the factoring company

00:54:42.000 --> 00:54:45.000
with money,

00:54:45.000 --> 00:54:48.000
and the factoring company provides it to you.

00:54:48.000 --> 00:54:51.000
Thus, you pay the bank a percentage

00:54:51.000 --> 00:54:54.000
and the factoring company a percentage

00:54:54.000 --> 00:54:57.000
for the factoring company's participation in the operation.

00:54:57.000 --> 00:55:00.000
Therefore, the factoring funds are more expensive

00:55:00.000 --> 00:55:03.000
than the bank funds.

00:55:03.000 --> 00:55:06.000
But we have already said that we have taken all the bank funds

00:55:06.000 --> 00:55:09.000
that we could get.

00:55:09.000 --> 00:55:12.000
The banks don't give us any more.

00:55:12.000 --> 00:55:15.000
We take the factoring company.

00:55:15.000 --> 00:55:18.000
We take the more expensive funds

00:55:18.000 --> 00:55:21.000
for not having the cheaper ones.

00:55:21.000 --> 00:55:24.000
But we have to pay for these funds anyway.

00:55:24.000 --> 00:55:27.000
The question arises,

00:55:27.000 --> 00:55:30.000
is any enterprise profitable

00:55:30.000 --> 00:55:33.000
with the credit funds or the factoring funds?

00:55:33.000 --> 00:55:36.000
The answer is simple, but we have to fixate it.

00:55:36.000 --> 00:55:39.000
The fact is that there is a profitability of the business.

00:55:39.000 --> 00:55:42.000
Any businessman gets a profit.

00:55:42.000 --> 00:55:45.000
There is a norm of the profit he gets.

00:55:45.000 --> 00:55:48.000
And the profitability of the business

00:55:48.000 --> 00:55:51.000
should be higher than the percentage

00:55:51.000 --> 00:55:54.000
that you pay for the factoring funds.

00:55:54.000 --> 00:55:57.000
In this case, if this condition is fulfilled,

00:55:57.000 --> 00:56:00.000
it is profitable for you to use the factoring funds.

00:56:00.000 --> 00:56:03.000
Therefore, no matter how much you take the factoring funds,

00:56:03.000 --> 00:56:06.000
the result will be profitable for you.

00:56:07.000 --> 00:56:10.000
This delta that arises between the profitability of your business

00:56:10.000 --> 00:56:13.000
and the percentage that you have to pay for the factoring funds

00:56:13.000 --> 00:56:16.000
is the result of your financial operations.

00:56:16.000 --> 00:56:19.000
And it brings additional income to the company.

00:56:19.000 --> 00:56:22.000
But if a businessman has a business

00:56:22.000 --> 00:56:25.000
that is less profitable than the percentage

00:56:25.000 --> 00:56:28.000
that you have to pay to the bank

00:56:28.000 --> 00:56:31.000
and the percentage that you have to pay to the bank

00:56:31.000 --> 00:56:34.000
and the percentage that you have to pay to the bank

00:56:35.000 --> 00:56:38.000
or the factoring company,

00:56:38.000 --> 00:56:41.000
it is not profitable to use these funds.

00:56:41.000 --> 00:56:44.000
Because you will pay more money for these funds

00:56:44.000 --> 00:56:47.000
than you will get from using them in the business.

00:56:52.000 --> 00:56:55.000
Therefore, before you go to the bank

00:56:55.000 --> 00:56:58.000
or the factoring company,

00:56:58.000 --> 00:57:01.000
you should look at the profitability of your business

00:57:02.000 --> 00:57:05.000
and compare it with the percentage that you have to pay

00:57:05.000 --> 00:57:08.000
for using the factoring funds.

00:57:08.000 --> 00:57:11.000
And, accordingly, make the appropriate decision.

00:57:16.000 --> 00:57:19.000
And at the end of our first question,

00:57:19.000 --> 00:57:22.000
I would like to make one small but very interesting remark.

00:57:22.000 --> 00:57:25.000
For small and medium-sized enterprises,

00:57:25.000 --> 00:57:28.000
there is a unique feature.

00:57:29.000 --> 00:57:32.000
It is so unique that it is a sin not to know about it.

00:57:32.000 --> 00:57:35.000
The fact is that these enterprises can build

00:57:35.000 --> 00:57:38.000
the system of current financial needs

00:57:38.000 --> 00:57:41.000
in such a way that it has a negative meaning.

00:57:41.000 --> 00:57:44.000
That is, to have more money flows

00:57:44.000 --> 00:57:47.000
than the need in these financial funds.

00:57:52.000 --> 00:57:55.000
Do you remember in our formula we said

00:57:55.000 --> 00:57:58.000
that the current need is determined

00:57:58.000 --> 00:58:01.000
by the need for reserves and debt.

00:58:01.000 --> 00:58:04.000
And the minus of the reserve and credit debt.

00:58:04.000 --> 00:58:07.000
Thus, if the credit debt exceeds the debt and reserves,

00:58:07.000 --> 00:58:10.000
you get into a unique situation

00:58:10.000 --> 00:58:13.000
when you, due to the business,

00:58:13.000 --> 00:58:16.000
due to the situation in the market,

00:58:16.000 --> 00:58:19.000
have borrowed more money

00:58:19.000 --> 00:58:22.000
than you need to borrow from others.

00:58:26.000 --> 00:58:29.000
Can you imagine?

00:58:29.000 --> 00:58:32.000
You are in a situation when you work

00:58:32.000 --> 00:58:35.000
exclusively with borrowed funds.

00:58:35.000 --> 00:58:38.000
And you did not specially borrow them.

00:58:38.000 --> 00:58:41.000
This is the situation in the market.

00:58:41.000 --> 00:58:44.000
You work in a situation when you are credited.

00:58:44.000 --> 00:58:47.000
And you are credited constantly.

00:58:47.000 --> 00:58:50.000
For an indefinite period.

00:58:50.000 --> 00:58:53.000
And in this situation you can be in for a very long time.

00:58:54.000 --> 00:58:57.000
And the middle enterprises should strive to get into it.

00:58:57.000 --> 00:59:00.000
When you are given more money with reserves,

00:59:00.000 --> 00:59:03.000
than you need to make the production process.

00:59:03.000 --> 00:59:06.000
And to give as a commodity credit to your customers.

00:59:18.000 --> 00:59:21.000
An amazing situation.

00:59:21.000 --> 00:59:25.000
And I am glad that the audience of this lecture is in such a state.